data.description: Wonderful turn-of-the-century style home in sought after Apple Orchard subdivision, featuring a large park, wide and well-lit sidewalks, a neighborhood gazebo, and pond with dock for fishing or just enjoying the view. Easy walk to downtown Fayetteville's restaurants and new 8-acre City Center Park which includes walking paths, playground, splash pad, dog park and library. Line Creek Brewing Bus Barn, City Cafe and ice cream shop. Take pride in owning this 3 bedroom, 2.5 bath cul-de-sac home with inviting front porch. Enter this gorgeous home and enjoy hardwood floors on the entire main floor and beautiful kitchen cabinets in this open floor plan with dining room. Large Master with walk-in-closet and double vanity sinks. Convenient to restaurants, grocery stores and walking trails. Qualifying Assumable 2.875 loan with approx. 28 years left, with approx. 55k down, monthly PI $1375.45. Home just painted inside.
